(266067, 8752, 263162, 'Mitho', 199, '', 1336305463, 'Thing is when a glock trigger is pressed the firing pin block is pushed upwards in conventional manner.\r\nBut in a caracal the firning block is placed laterally so when thrigger is pulled the firing pin block is pushed side ways thats why theres that shiver.if u watch closely the shiver is there before the firing pin starts to protude out from behind.\r\nThis was done to improve the glock trigger giving a caracal a more crisp trigger.', 1, 0, '141.0.9.220', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
