(465637, 12736, 465601, 'Bhatti1965', 7456, '', 1415695826, '[QUOTE=faisalfareedi;465601]Good Day everyone,\nsomeone quoted me Colt''s M4, just wanna know how can easily judge the genuineness of it, and what are the major differences in the original one and fake one, pls elaborate, thanks in advance, try to post some pics soon too\nRegards[/QUOTE]\nFaisalfareedi, detach the upper receiver from the lower receiver first and look inside and check whether the lower parts such as the trigger mechanism and hammer are all polished and original like real ones, look up for pics of the originals online. Also look at the front site and look for a mark that says "F". See the finish, how good it is, look at the buffer tube and see that it is not rough and shabby looking but shiny and smooth just like a colt has it. Look down the barrel and check whether the chrome lining is intact. There is really no other way to verify, but what I can tell you for sure is if you see and hold a real one and open it up you will know it is an original. Please kindly also share the price so that people on this forum can benefit from the info and add it to the list of AR-15s available in Pak. Please also tell the city, you need not tell the dealer.', 1, 0, '121.218.106.203', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
