(465636, 11821, 380456, 'Bhatti1965', 7456, '', 1415695195, 'Hello Pete,\n  I love big game hunting and have done it in the USA in the past, but never in the UK, I in fact did not know it was something the English readily did! Call it my ignorance. I wish we could have properly regulated game reserves here in Pakistan, since hunting in all the reserves is illegal. If one wants to find big game they have to go far up north to hunt Markhor and big horn sheep. \n  Our firearm laws are a bit different from the UK in that we dont have to show reason to acquire a firearm license we merely have to mention the "main" purpose we will be using it for whether we use it for that purpose or not is totally our decision. As far as semi auto centre fire rifles are concerned we are allowed to have any rifle that has a .22inch barrel diameter and is semi automatic, which includes a host of different calibers hence people in Pakistan can own AR-15s how ever this government is bent upon changing that. We can also easily own and carry handguns concealed which is also different from the UK laws. \n  The terrain in your pics is beautiful I hope I can one day come and hunt there.', 1, 0, '121.218.106.203', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
